Ireland to Announce Three-Year Budget Plan in Autumn, Post Says

-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 
2011-08-21T13:17:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-21/ireland-to-announce-three-year-budget-plan-in-autumn-post-says.html
Ireland’s government will announce
this “autumn” details on plans to raise taxes and cut spending
over the next three years, the Sunday Business Post reported,
citing “senior sources” it didn’t identify.  The budget details are intended to give clarity to markets
and consumers over the government’s plans and boost confidence
in its commitment to honor its pledges to the  International
Monetary Fund  and the European Union, the Dublin-based newspaper
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
